pd_0_com_0text: An adventurer! An evil necromancer awakened from its slumber and it is recuiting skeletons to join his army. I need your help...
pd_1_com_1text: I don't really care, I just want to get out.
pd_2_com_0text: An ancient ritual was performed in this temple to bless weapons and make them stronger to undeads. Or perhaps you are feeling brave and you want to face the enemy right away...
pd_3_com_0text: Do you see that purple fog? It's the only way out and until someone worthy can face the necromancer, I will keep it shut.
pd_4_com_0text: So I really have no choice here...
pd_5_com_0text: You have indeed. You can defeat the necromancer by facing him right away if you are so brave, or eager to die some might say. Legends say that the one who defeats a necromancer on his own becomes incredibly stronger.
pd_6_com_0text: Well, I'm your guy then. Bards will sing my deeds!
pd_6_com_1text: Isn't there another way? Perhaps somehow I could exploit a weak spot...
pd_7_com_0text: Good luck to you brave hero. The door will open for you: Once you go there, there is now turning back. Are you sure?
pd_8_com_0text: Yes. I am. His power will be mine.
pd_8_com_1text: Didn't you speak about another approach?
pd_8_com_2text: <Exit> I need to think about it...
pd_9_com_0text: Well, there is. If you manage to find the old altar in the temple on your right, you can bless your weapon. I would perform the ritual on my own, I am afraid ghost cannot do it. With a single strike, the necromancer will turn into stone and his magic won't work properly.
pd_11_com_0text:
Be aware that while you will be granted access to our old temple,
the our lord of light will demand the necromancer's soul.
pd_12_com_0text: Fair enough, I'd like to see this temple.
pd_12_com_1text: I changed my mind, I'd rather risk my life to obtain glory and power.
pd_13_com_0text: The green barrier will go down for you: Once you go there, there is no turning back. Are you sure?
pd_14_com_0text: Yes. I am. I'll find the altar and bless this sword.
pd_14_com_1text: <Exit> I need to think about it...
pd_15_com_0text: The purple barrier will go down for you: Once you go there, there is now turning back. Are you sure?
pd_16_com_0text: Well, I have some choices to think about...
